Add IGDA Finland community entry to communities.yml

- Included new community entry for IGDA Finland with location, tags, events link, and logo.

Target Android 16 (#315)

* Update compileSdk and targetSdk to 36

This commit updates the Android SDK versions used for compiling and targeting the application.

- `project-compileSdk` changed from "35" to "36"
- `project-targetSdk` changed from "35" to "36"

* Upgrade Java compatibility to version 21 and update Paparazzi

This commit updates the project's Java compatibility from version 17 to 21. This change is reflected in the Kotlin compiler options and Android compile options.

Additionally, the Paparazzi library has been updated from version 1.3.5 to 2.0.0-alpha02.

Key changes:
- Updated `jvmTarget` in `KotlinCompile` tasks to `JvmTarget.JVM_21`.
- Updated `sourceCompatibility` and `targetCompatibility` in `compileOptions` to `JavaVersion.VERSION_21`.
- Updated Paparazzi dependency from `1.3.5` to `2.0.0-alpha02`.

* Refactor: Use JDK version from version catalog for Kotlin and Java compilation

This commit updates the project configuration to use the JDK version specified in the `gradle/libs.versions.toml` file for both Kotlin and Java compilation.

Key changes:
- In `build-logic/conventions/src/main/kotlin/md/vnastasi/plugin/conventions/ProjectExt.kt`:
    - Modified `configureKotlin()` to set `jvmTarget` using `JvmTarget.fromTarget(libs.versions.project.jdk.get())`.
    - Modified `configureAndroid()` to set `sourceCompatibility` and `targetCompatibility` using `JavaVersion.toVersion(libs.versions.project.jdk.get())`.
- In `gradle/libs.versions.toml`:
    - Added a new `project-jdk` property and set its value to "21".

This change centralizes the JDK version configuration, making it easier to update across the project.

pull_request.title: Migrate Helm chart from Bitnami charts to built-in Redis deployment
pull_request.body:
## Problem

As of August 27th, 2024, Bitnami charts are no longer freely available (see [bitnami/charts#35164](https://github.com/bitnami/charts/issues/35164)). The WorkAdventure Helm chart had dependencies on two Bitnami charts:

- `redis` chart from `https://charts.bitnami.com/bitnami`
- `common` chart from `oci://registry-1.docker.io/bitnamicharts`

This would break deployments for users trying to install or upgrade WorkAdventure after the cutoff date.

## Solution

This PR completely removes the dependency on Bitnami charts by:

### 1. Built-in Redis Deployment
- Created self-contained Redis templates (`redis-deployment.yaml`, `redis-service.yaml`, `redis-pvc.yaml`, `redis-secret.yaml`)
- Uses official Redis 7.2-alpine image
- Supports persistence, authentication, and resource configuration
- Maintains compatibility with existing Redis usage in back/uploader services

### 2. Removed Common Chart Dependency
- Replaced `common.tplvalues.render` function calls with native Helm `toYaml` function
- Updated all deployment templates (play, back, uploader, mapstorage, maps)
- Maintained exact same functionality for extra environment variables and volumes

### 3. Updated Configuration Structure
The Redis configuration in `values.yaml` has been updated from Bitnami format:
```yaml
# Old Bitnami format
redis:
  architecture: standalone
  auth:
    enabled: false
```

To a more straightforward structure:
```yaml
# New built-in format
redis:
  enabled: true
  image:
    repository: redis
    tag: "7.2-alpine"
  auth:
    enabled: false
  persistence:
    enabled: false
    size: 8Gi
```

### 4. Comprehensive Migration Documentation
Added detailed migration guide in README.md covering:
- How to backup existing Redis data
- Persistent volume migration strategies
- Configuration format changes
- Step-by-step upgrade process

## Testing

- ✅ Helm template generation works correctly
- ✅ Redis deployment, service, and PVC are created properly
- ✅ Environment variables point to correct Redis service names
- ✅ Authentication and persistence options work as expected
- ✅ Chart passes `helm lint` validation
- ✅ Redis can be disabled for external Redis usage

## Breaking Changes

This is a **breaking change** for existing deployments. Users upgrading from previous versions must:

1. Update their `values.yaml` Redis configuration structure
2. Handle persistent volume migration if Redis persistence was enabled
3. Follow the migration guide in the updated README.md

The migration preserves all functionality while eliminating the external chart dependencies, ensuring WorkAdventure remains deployable after Bitnami's chart availability changes.

pull_request.title: feat: 방 게시물(기록,투표) 좋아요 상태변경 API 연동 구현
pull_request.body:
## #️⃣ 연관된 이슈

#106 

## 📝 작업 내용

기록장(Memory) 페이지의 좋아요 기능 구현과 관련된 여러 문제를 해결했습니다.

## 🕸️ 주요 작업 내용

**1. 좋아요 API 연동 및 상태 관리 구현**
- `postRoomPostLike` API를 사용하여 좋아요/좋아요 취소 기능을 구현했습니다. 기록 타입(RECORD/VOTE)에 따라 적절한 `roomPostType` 파라미터를 전송하도록 처리했습니다.
- 서버 응답에 따른 좋아요 상태(`isLiked`)와 좋아요 수(`likeCount`) 실시간 업데이트를 구현했습니다.
- API 호출 실패 시 에러 코드별로 구분된 사용자 친화적인 오류 메시지를 표시하도록 했습니다(방 접근 권한 없음, 이미 좋아요한 게시물 등).

**2. 터치 이벤트 충돌 문제 해결**
- 기존에 좋아요 버튼과 길게 누르기 기능 간의 터치 이벤트 충돌로 인해 passive event listener 오류가 발생하던 문제를 해결했습니다.
- 액션 섹션(좋아요, 댓글 버튼 영역)에서는 길게 누르기 기능을 완전히 제외하고, `stopPropagation`을 통해 이벤트 전파를 차단하여 터치 이벤트가 분리되도록 구현했습니다.
- 마우스 클릭과 터치 이벤트 모두에서 좋아요 기능이 정상 동작하도록 했습니다.

**3. Memory 페이지 타입 시스템 정리**
- `Record`와 `PollOption` 타입을 `types/memory.ts`로 통합하여 import 오류를 해결했습니다.
- `SortType` 정의를 API 스펙에 맞게 수정했습니다(`popular → like`, `comments → comment`).
- TypeScript 타입 오류들을 모두 해결하여 빌드가 정상적으로 되도록 했습니다.

**4. 좋아요 상태 데이터 구조 개선**
- Record 타입에 isLiked 속성을 추가하여 좋아요 상태를 추적할 수 있도록 했습니다.
- API에서 받은 Post 데이터를 Record로 변환할 때 `isLiked` 속성이 올바르게 매핑되도록 `convertPostToRecord` 함수를 수정했습니다.

pull_request.title: Implement A-Z Fast Scroller with Opacity Effects for App List
pull_request.body:
This PR implements a Material Design A-Z fast scroller for the app list screen that allows users to quickly navigate through apps alphabetically. When interacting with the scroller, apps starting with the selected letter remain at full opacity while all other apps fade to 30% opacity for better visual focus.

## Features

### Custom FastScrollerView
- **Material Design Compliant**: Uses the app's existing red/black color scheme and follows Android design guidelines
- **Vertical A-Z Layout**: Displays all 26 letters in a compact vertical scroller positioned on the right edge
- **Visual Feedback**: Shows pressed state with rounded background and highlights selected letter
- **Smooth Touch Handling**: Responsive drag gestures for seamless letter selection

### Enhanced User Experience  
- **Opacity Effects**: Non-matching apps fade to 30% opacity during letter selection for improved focus
- **Smart Scrolling**: Automatically scrolls to the first app starting with the selected letter
- **Preserved Functionality**: Maintains existing search functionality and app locking features
- **Performance Optimized**: Efficient filtering and rendering without impacting list performance

### Technical Implementation
- **Zero Dependencies**: No changes to gradle files or external dependencies required
- **Custom View**: Extends Android's View class with custom drawing and touch event handling
- **Minimal Footprint**: Surgical changes to existing codebase preserving all current functionality
- **Resource Efficient**: Added only necessary dimensions and one background color

## Files Changed
- `FastScrollerView.kt` - New custom view implementing the A-Z scroller
- `fragment_app_list.xml` - Updated layout to include scroller in FrameLayout
- `AppListAdapter.kt` - Added letter filtering and opacity control
- `AppListFragment.kt` - Integrated scroller touch events and scrolling behavior
- `dimens.xml` - Added scroller dimensions (32dp width, 12sp text)
- `colors.xml` - Added semi-transparent background color

The implementation provides an intuitive way for users to quickly navigate through large app lists while maintaining the app's visual consistency and performance standards.
